CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, Philadelphia edition, May 11, 1940, pg. 15 reads: " A.M.E.'s Open General Conference In Detroit...No.10 - The report of the Sunday School union was read by its secretary-treasurer, Dr. E.A. Selby."
TitMainTitle: Dr. E. A. Selby wearing dark suit and ribbon on lapel, standing at microphone in Ebenezer AME Church for AME General Conference, Detroit
